column5: Welll it was a bumpy day on the pond yesterday but the fish were bitting 1 Coho and the lakers were hungry here are a couple pics ...little to bumpy for taken pictures ...fished the bar for the end of the trip managed some nice lakers 28fow 17 down on the riggers with Mic Stinger did the best water temp was 52 ..I will be out all next week searching for Kings ...dam i love Lake Ontario
Very nice. I have yet to catch my first laker, but hope to do so this year jigging for whitties on Simcoe.
nice fish...certainly does look a little "choppy" out there...lol.
